description:
The DLQ endpoints (/api/dlq/requeue/{queue_name}, /api/dlq/requeue-all/{queue_name}, DELETE /api/dlq/{queue_name}) allow destructive operations (requeuing and deleting jobs) without any authentication. In a multi-user or network-accessible deployment, this could allow unauthorized users to manipulate the job queues.

Affected endpoints:
- POST /api/dlq/requeue/{queue_name}
- POST /api/dlq/requeue-all/{queue_name}  
- DELETE /api/dlq/{queue_name}

Recommendation: Add API key or token-based authentication for admin-level endpoints.

Create a React hook to listen for service_status WebSocket events.

## File to create
- `frontend/src/hooks/useServiceStatus.ts`

## Hook Interface
```typescript
interface ServiceStatus {
  service: 'redis' | 'rtdetr' | 'nemotron';
  status: 'healthy' | 'unhealthy' | 'restarting' | 'restart_failed' | 'failed';
  message?: string;
  timestamp: string;
}

function useServiceStatus(): {
  services: Record<string, ServiceStatus>;
  hasUnhealthy: boolean;
}
```

## Behavior
- Subscribe to WebSocket on mount
- Filter for type: "service_status" messages
- Maintain map of latest status per service
- Compute hasUnhealthy flag for quick checks

## Acceptance Criteria
- Hook subscribes to existing WebSocket connection
- Status updates trigger re-renders
- Handles reconnection gracefully
